!begin_node (!kw [hyphen])
!html_name cmd_hyphen

Set global hyphenation mark.

!begin_xlist [(!TYPEPOSITION)]

!item [(!TYPEPOSITION)] (!COMMAND), (!PREAMBLE)

!item [(!SYNTAX)] (!T)!/hyphen (!WORD)(!t)

!item [(!DESCRIPTION)]
You can set hyphenation marks ((!code [!/-])) with this command for
a word for the whole text. The example shows how to tell UDO where
it is allowed to split up the word ""hyphenation"".

!item [(!SEEALSO)]
(!link [Hyphenation] [Hyphenation]), (!KW [sloppy]), (!KW [fussy]), (!K1 [//-])

!end_xlist

(!EXAMPLE)
(!EXAMPLE_BEGIN)
!begin_verbatim
!hyphen syl!/-labi!/-fi!/-ca!/-tion
!end_verbatim
(!EXAMPLE_END)

!end_node
